<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Silverboltt</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-16 13:26:31</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The ghoulbane is better than a rusty short sword</font></td></tr></table>
<BR>
<table width=100%>
<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Aldamir Bloodmyst</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-07-18 04:32:25</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>Today I camped Ghoulbane with two friends of mine for a total of myabe 4 hours. The group consisted of myself (a 37 warrior), a 36 enchanter, and a 34 druid.<BR>
Getting into the room was easy as I was the only one of us who was KOS to the froggies. There are 3 spawns in the room that were almost always green to me (in other words under level 29 MOBs), and the spawn time of the area is 15 minutes. One of the 3 spawns seems to have about a 30% chance of being the Lord.<BR>
<BR>
The Lord himself was the only danger to us, as he sees invis, has Lay Hands, has massive channeling, and loves to spam heal himself when he gets low.<BR>
He hit for maybe 70 dmg maximum.<BR>
<BR>
He spawned 3 times in those 4 hours, giving us 2 tin foil, errr Silver Plated bracers, and a single Ghoulbane. (When he has the ghoulbane you can tell, it looks like a rusty 2 hander. Just pray that it isn't REALLY a rusty 2 hander he's using :)<BR>
<BR>
I doubt a group with any mid or low 20s in it would stand a chance in this room, just because when Lord spawns, who is mid or low 30s, no one's spells would hold and he'd eat the tanks for breakfast. Thanks to his healing prowess he's a rather long fight. A well balanced group of high 20s, on the other hand, could get themselves a few Ghoulbanes and some good exp in this room.<BR>
<BR>
Well those are just my experiences, I hope those of you seeking this sword find this information useful.<BR>
<BR>
~Aldamir Bloodmyst<BR>
37 Hobbit Warrior<BR>
Sacrament -- Povar</font></td></tr></table>
