<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Merkvah</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-08-09 11:49:18</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>The camp could be easily done at lvl 30 with a group of 4.  For a paladin, the frogloks do not aggro to you (they con indifferent) untill you kill one, so my group and I walked all the way to the shin lord room, figured out exactly what we wanted to do and where we wanted to pull too (a little room close to the Shin Lord room where only ONE froggie spawns, a warrior who conned blue to me at 30), and THEN we killed the warrior, pulled from the pit room, then pulled from the shin lord room.  it was a CAKEWALK.  Stay organized, and you'll get single pulls every time.  <BR>
<BR>
Unfortunately, the shin lord is a rare spawn, and GB is his rare drop, so we got none in the three hours I camped him before going permanently link dead.  I will have to go back again to get one, but it was too easy to wait a minute past 30.  My next paladin will go at lvl 25 or 27.  <BR>
<BR>
Merkvah Holyblade<BR>
